  "commentary": "With SPX at 6607.45 trading just above the 6606 GEX flip and massive positive gamma walls at 6605 (+9B) and 6600 (+7.9B), dealers are aggressively selling into this rally to hedge their long gamma positions. The PIN regime confirms dealers will provide heavy resistance here, especially with spot sitting right on top of the max positive gamma strike at 6605 where they'll be most active sellers. Watch for mean reversion back toward 6600-6605 as the towering positive GEX walls should act as magnets, while any break below 6600 could accelerate toward the negative gamma pocket at 6500 where dealer buying would kick in.\n\nBottom line: expect a pullback from current levels with strong support emerging around 6600-6605.",
